##Epidemic Prevention and control, back to work on the broad picture of the north

Wechat media-fox

Features, for those who insist on serious reading options. Sohu News Extreme Day studio.

Photo and caption by Lu Meng
Editor | 林鹏

With the extension of the end of the holiday, the epidemic, "safe return" has become the hearts of every traveler's expectations.

In Beijing Railway Station, the D31 train from Dalian pulls into the station, and every passenger who gets off the train has a passenger information registration form in his hand. The form filled in each passenger's name, Identity Card number, train number, address and other information, at the exit of the staff uniform recovery.

"there were not many people on the train, but we were very nervous along the way and did not dare to speak, hoping that the epidemic would pass as soon as possible, " said a passenger surnamed Xie.

According to media reports, Beijing Beijing Capital International Airport, Daxing Airport, Beijing Railway Station, Beijing West Railway Station and Beijing South Station have all increased the frequency of disinfection in public areas, equipped with intelligent infrared temperature detection system and hand-held thermometer, carry out temperature measurement for passengers entering and leaving port and entering and leaving station. Passengers with abnormal body temperature need to go to the observation room for observation and treatment.

In the Shanghai Hongqiao Railway Station, arriving passengers are required to download the Shanghai "health cloud APP" in advance, scan the Qr code on the train seat or pay attention to the "Shanghai Railway Bureau Wechat Public Account" , to complete the "health registration to Shanghai personnel. ".

"according to the monitoring and analysis of big data, from now until the end of the Spring Festival travel rush, that is, until February 18,160 million people are expected to return to work one after another, " Xu Yahua, director of the Ministry of Transport of the People's Republic of China, said at a news conference of the State Council's Joint Prevention and control mechanism against COVID-19 pneumonia.

The data showed that as of February 10, the railway authorities found a total of 7,573 passengers with fever in the process of checking in and out of the stations, and more than 1,800 batches of close contacts on board the train in cooperation with the authorities in identifying or suspected cases.

Tourists wearing face masks return to Beijing Railway Station Square on February 6,2020.

Passengers take pictures in Beijing Railway Station Square on February 6,2020.

Passengers wear double face masks to protect themselves at the Beijing Railway Station Station on February 6,2020.

Passengers leave the platform in Beijing Railway Station on February 6,2020.

On February 6,2020, every passenger was required to fill out a passenger information registration form.

At the Beijing Railway Station Departure Gate, each exit is equipped with infrared temperature measuring equipment. Security officers will check the body temperature of every outbound passenger and take back the information registration form that the passenger has filled in.

If a passenger's body temperature exceeds 37.3 °C, the station staff will take him to the observation room at the exit of Beijing Station for further examination.

A worker disinfects a building in Beijing South Railway Station February 7,2020.

An outgoing passenger checks in with his family on the phone in Beijing South Railway Station February 7,2020.

Workers disinfect a platform at the South Station station in Guangzhou on Feb. 7. In order to do a good job in the prevention and control of COVID-19 pneumonia, Guangzhou South Station has stepped up the frequency of disinfection in key areas of the station to ensure the safety of passengers. PHOTO: Xinhua

Passengers arrive at Guangzhou South Railway Station on February 8. (photo: Chinanews.com)

People wearing face masks embrace at Guangzhou South Railway Station on Feb. 9. (photo: Southern Metropolis Daily)

As the requirements for the prevention and control of the epidemic continue to escalate, passengers entering and leaving the two major international airports in Shanghai will be strictly tested. Passengers will be required to fill out the "declaration card for the health of entry and exit personnel" regardless of whether they leave or enter the country, so as to prevent the importation of the epidemic, more stringent export control measures. PHOTO: CNN

Most international flights are concentrated in the Shanghai Pudong International Airport, and Shanghai Customs Health and Quarantine Workers Frequently Board flights for boarding and inspection. PHOTO: CNN

On February 9, the Shanghai Hongqiao Railway Station took temperature readings of departing and arriving passengers, who were also required to download the Shanghai "health cloud APP" and scan qr codes on train seats in advance, to complete the "health registration to Shanghai personnel. ". PHOTO: Xinhua

Shanghai Hongqiao Railway Station, the registration information shows Class A passengers, that is, those departing from or passing through Hubei, need to register, and then transport to the West Square by a unified shuttle bus, after the centralized check point is again approved, inform them of the 14-day home quarantine, and inform them of the implementation of the relevant work measures in the community where they live. (picture: view the news)

On the afternoon of February 9,2020, when entering the intersection of Shanghai Expressway, drivers of every vehicle entering the checkpoint are required to fill out a "health registration form" . Traffic police and volunteers will take body temperature of the people inside the vehicle, verification Documents and monitoring whether the key areas to guard the vehicle into Shanghai First Line of Defense. (picture: view the news)

Newly deplaned passengers at Terminal T2 in Beijing Capital International Airport, on February 7,2020.

A passenger wears disposable gloves outside Terminal T2 in Beijing Capital International Airport, on February 7,2020.

Travellers returning from Thailand pack up masks they have brought back from abroad and give away some of the remaining medical masks to airport cleaners at no cost in Beijing Capital International Airport, on February 7,2020.

Security personnel at Daxing Airport check the body temperature of every passenger as they enter and exit the airport via infrared equipment on February 6,2020.

Most restaurants in the airport close early during the holidays, and airport staff choose fast food for dinner.

The taxi lines outside the airport have gone out of fashion.

A taxi driver waiting outside the airport. Traffic was down, and he sometimes had to wait five hours to pick up a passenger, an experience he had not had before.
